# Add patterns of files dvc should ignore, which could improve
# the performance. Learn more at
# https://dvc.org/doc/user-guide/dvcignore

# Ultralytics writes label/image caches next to the labels (e.g.
# labels/train.cache, labels/val.cache) the first time it scans a dataset.
# Without this rule, every `dvc repro` sees data/datasets/v{X}/ as modified
# after `train` runs and wants to rerun the whole stage.
*.cache
